docs.description:
Indicator Description [Net Cash Flow from Financing]: A component of [NCF] representing the amount of cash inflow (outflow) from financing activities, from continuing and discontinued operations. Principal components of financing cash flow are: issuance (purchase) of equity shares, issuance (repayment) of debt securities, and payment of dividends & other cash distributions.
